commit.message: Define our own copy of SDL_clamp for people with old versions of SDL2

Switch to SDL_clamp

Also remove max/min private functions from shape

SDL introduced this macro a few years ago and I think that's what's
caused this bug (despite there being no changes to Apricots in the mean
time). I don't quite understand *why* it breaks as std::clamp work the
exact same way.

Relevant SDL commits:
- https://github.com/libsdl-org/SDL/commit/35c1bbfa49b1247c2c6240f7f95871f3b3331874
- https://github.com/libsdl-org/SDL/commit/fbc364908a4fd4644e96377ed488811f025cf36b

Fixes #41

Fix linter issues

- remove random newline
- properly initialise structs
Ignore autogenerated files

Don't call aclocal in bootstrap

autoreconf already does that. When/if we want to update our m4 files we
can call aclocal --install manually
